---
description: Python venv and keep requirements.txt in sync with pyproject.toml
alwaysApply: true
---

When working with Python projects, check for and activate a virtual environment (`.venv` or `venv`) before `pip install`. If none exists, remind the user to create one.

Maintain both `requirements.txt` (pip) and `pyproject.toml` (uv). Update one when the other has been edited.

Use the correct activation for the OS. On Linux with fish:

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate.fish
```

On Windows (PowerShell):

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
```
